Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The Nigerian Electricity Regulatory Commission on Sunday announced its readiness to establish a think-tank to be saddled with the task of providing solutions that would end cases of blackouts across the country. According to the commission, the team would consist of experts from the United States of America, other African countries, Nigeria, among others. The Chairman, NERC, Prof. James Momoh, disclosed this in Abuja. Copyright PUNCH.
